post_text: Another awesome group for our kiddos!!
shared_text:
Dina Bishara‚ÄéWest Branch Iowa Community
October 23, 2018 at 8:20 AM ¬∑

Good morning! I am the Program Specialist at Big Brothers Big Sisters of Johnson County. For the past few years we have enjoyed a special partnership with West Branch schools and are able to support 12-15 one-to-one mentoring relationships in West Branch. Half of the equation is identifying "Littles" (kids in need of positive, fun relationship with an adult mentor). The other half is finding committed, compassionate "Bigs" who are interested in being a positive influence in someone's life. Please email me or comment if you are interested in learning more about being a Big in West Branch, or if you know a child in West Branch who may love to be a Little: dina@bbbsjc.org

Learn more about Big Brothers Big Sisters here: https://www.bbbsjc.org/

Not able to physically volunteer at the event? That's okay! We would love your baked goods!!

Monster Mash has sold hundreds of fun desserts the last 2 years and we plan to sell several hundred more on the 27th! Who has those awesome baking skills (or incredible bakery section SHOPPING skills üòÇ) and would like to help by donating sweets? This is a big money maker as each individual piece sells for $1-2 each. We have found the unique and fun desserts sell quickest- but who wouldn't turn down an amazing chocolate chip cookie bought from the store?... I know I wouldn't! üôàüôâüôä

Some favorites from last year were cake balls, dirt and worms, Halloween cookies, rice crispy treats, and anything that looked spooky!

Please sign up below (we are expecting to sell around 400 individual desserts if numbers are the same as last year):

Now that school is off to a good start, and everyone is getting into their routines it is time to hold our first PTO meeting of the school year!

ALL parents are invited- I am talking to you, Preschool, Kindergarten, New student, and any parents who HAVEN'T been to a meeting before! üòÅ

This is a very laid back meeting that will be held on Wednesday, September 19th 6:30 pm at Mexico Lindo. Feel free to order food and drinks!

This meeting is so important as it sets our year up for success. This is the meeting where we decide what events and fundraisers will are going to do this year.

Do you wish there was a spring carnival, family movie night, tech night, craft night, father/daughter mother/son dance? Do you have a great idea for fundraising? These are just some ideas I've thrown out to get us started. We need parents and members of the community who are excited for these events and fundraising. Coming to this meeting helps get your voice heard and let's us get these events on the calendar.

Please mark your calendars and we will see you next Wednesday!

post_text: Our new Superintendent has been announced! West Branch PTO is looking forward to getting to know our new leader. Thank you to everyone involved in the process of selecting our new Superintendent. Marty will be a great addition to the West Branch Community!
shared_text:
West Branch Community Schools
May 24, 2018 at 11:56 AM ¬∑

The West Branch School district is pleased to announce that a contract for Superintendent of West Branch School District has been offered to Marty Jimmerson.

Marty Jimmerson is currently the Superintendent at AGWSR School District and also serves as High School Principal. He has worked in the AGWSR School District since 2014. Jimmerson has been in education for 22 years, including 9 years as a Principal at St. Ansgar Community Schools and Ballard Community School District. Marty and his wife, Jess, have three grown daughters - Bryanna and twins, Miranda and Mariah.

There were 39 applications for the position. The board interviewed 6 semi-finalists on May 19, 2018. Three finalists were interviewed by several stakeholders groups on May 21,22 and 23. Jimmerson will assume the duties of superintendent beginning July 1, 2018.
text:
Our new Superintendent has been announced! West Branch PTO is looking forward to getting to know our new leader. Thank you to everyone involved in the process of selecting our new Superintendent. Marty will be a great addition to the West Branch Community!

West Branch Community Schools
May 24, 2018 at 11:56 AM ¬∑

The West Branch School district is pleased to announce that a contract for Superintendent of West Branch School District has been offered to Marty Jimmerson.

Marty Jimmerson is currently the Superintendent at AGWSR School District and also serves as High School Principal. He has worked in the AGWSR School District since 2014. Jimmerson has been in education for 22 years, including 9 years as a Principal at St. Ansgar Community Schools and Ballard Community School District. Marty and his wife, Jess, have three grown daughters - Bryanna and twins, Miranda and Mariah.

There were 39 applications for the position. The board interviewed 6 semi-finalists on May 19, 2018. Three finalists were interviewed by several stakeholders groups on May 21,22 and 23. Jimmerson will assume the duties of superintendent beginning July 1, 2018.

May 23, 2018 at 11:50 AM ¬∑

Chip Away at Hunger Golf Tournament

The West Branch Operation Backpack program will be hosting its 2nd annual golf tournament fundraiser on Saturday, August 11th at Cedar's Edge Golf Course. The program discretely provides easy to prepare meals and snacks each Friday of the school year to elementary students in need of food support right here in our community. It costs nearly $200 annually to support one student's participation in the program. The program and is seeking both sponsorships and golfers for the tournament. If you are interested in sponsoring or participating in the tournament, please contact Jess Burger at 643-7211.

post_text:
West Branch PTO was able to provide our teachers and staff with a new Keurig after the one they had stopped working.

This is the second appliance PTO has replaced this year in the schools. Earlier this year we replaced the popcorn machine our students and staff love so much.

Please continue to support the PTO with upcoming events and fundraising. We have fundraising goals that we still need to reach!

You can help by buying raffle tickets, participating in the Bear Stampede, being a family sponsor, or reaching out to use to make a monetary donation.

If you want to help by volunteering or donating items for Bear Stampede please let us know by commenting or email westbranchpto@gmail.com. We need volunteers to make our events a success.

We have plans for a new all inclusive playground item that will be installed before next school year! We will give more information on it in the coming weeks.

We are able to provide our school with the *extras* thanks to support from families and local businesses.

Thank you for your continued support,

West Branch PTO

post_text:
I'd like to invite the West Branch PTO & parents to an event this Thursday evening in Coralville at the Kirkwood Regional Center. The goal of the event is to rally public school parents in a non-partisan pro-public school manner.

Parents for Great Iowa Schools will be presenting about how current legislation could affect Iowa public schools and what parents can do to have a voice. The goal is to provide updates in a non-partisan, easy to understand format - perfect for people who love public schools, but are a little new to the political process when it comes to advocating.

Please help spread this invite to your community in an effort to turn out a great attendance and support of public schools in Eastern Iowa. There is an event created on Facebook if you'd like to share it on social media. SearchEastern Iowa Corridor Public School Rally

Feel free to reach out with any questions.

Thanks!

Jodi Yeggy

Parent & School Board Member

West Branch

post_text:
It's that exciting time of year again - the Bear Stampede is almost here! May 11 will be our 4th annual 5k, 10k, 1 mile and Kids' Fun Run to benefit West Branch PTO. If you've done it before, you know it's a blast - don't miss the early deadline for a cheaper rate - it's this Friday!

If you have never joined us for the race, you are missing out. The kids have an absolute blast at the Fun Run and get a race t-shirt and ribbon. Herky should be making an appearance again this year!!

EVERY 5k and 10k runner/walker will enjoy home baked goods after the race and get to randomly pick a prize from all of the great donations we've been busy collecting. You can win things like an overnight stay at Riverside Casino, a We Run Gift Card, a family package for the CR Kernals, Panchero's Burritos, McDonald's Ice Cream, Salon packages, Carr Chiropractic consult and adjustment, and much, much more. Every one is a winner!!

The website below has a link to online registration as well as a form you can print and mail.

post_text: A big Thanks to everyone who came to the Brick Arch Winery on Saturday night for the PTO Adult 80's Bash. It was fun seeing the big hair, poufy dresses and tight rolled jeans. A BIG shout out to Destiny Borland-Moon for taking awesome pics and Pete Swisher-AKA DJ Pete Steel for playing awesome 80 tunes!!!

post_text: There is 1 more day to purchase your advanced tickets for Saturday's PTO Adult Prom at the Brick Arch Winery for $15. They will also be available at the door for $20 per per person. Hope to see you there!!
